Lionel Corporation was an American toy manufacturer and retailer that was in business from 1900-1995. Founded as an electrical novelties company, Lionel specialized in various products throughout its existence, but toy trains and model railroads were its main claim to fame.[1] Lionel trains, produced from 1900 to 1969, drew admiration from model railroaders around the world for the solidity of their construction and the authenticity of their detail. During its peak years in the 1950s, the company sold 25 million worth of trains per year.[2] In 2006, Lionel's electric train, along with the Easy-Bake Oven, became the first electric toy inducted into the National Toy Hall of Fame.
Lionel remains the most enduring brand name associated with model trains in the United States, its products prized by collectors. Today, Lionel, LLC owns all of the trademarks and most of the product rights associated with the Lionel Corporation; there is, however, no direct connection between the two companies. (Credit: Wikipedia)

A little history on the Hi-Flier Kite company;
It was launched in Decatur in the 1920s by Harvey A. Sellers. He was a paper supplies salesman who made kites out of samples to amuse kids. Then he felt the tug of opportunity and began production in his basement.
His grandson, John Sellers, says the business had soared to be the nation's top paper kite-maker by the 1960s. Hi-Flier had a factory and 200 employees. A large part of their business was printing advertising kites for companies like Kroger stores.
Sellers father, Harvey Sellers Jr., later took over and Sellers' brother, Stuart, worked in it before running his own printing business. Sellers worked for Hi-Flier briefly and then joined the Navy in the early 1970s. That's when he got a call saying the business was sold.

Product name: 1970s LEVIS Jeans 23 Waist Single Stitch Bartacks 302
Description:
Vintage 70s Levi's 302 jeans. The 302 style is the child/student version of the 505 zip fly jean.  Waist measures 23 inches.
All jeans are listed according to the actual waist measurement, NOT the tag size. Vintage Levi's were designed to shrink. The actual measured size will generally be 2-3 inches smaller than the tag size. 
Actual measurements:  
Waist 23"
Rise 9.5"
Hips 32"
Inseam 27"
#03043
See size guide before ordering // DO NOT order your normal size
Jeans and shorts are listed according to the actual measured waist size. For an accurate fit, measure your waist just below your belly button. 
SIZE GUIDE
Modern Jeans .................. Vintage Jeans
Size 00/24 ........................ 24-26"
Size  0/25 ......................... 25-27"
Size  2/26 ......................... 26-29"
Size  4/27 ......................... 27-30"
Size  6/28 ......................... 29-31"
Size  8/29 ......................... 31-33"
Size  10/30/31 .................. 32-34"
Size  12/32 ....................... 34-36"
Size  14/33/34 ................. 35-36"  
The measurements are taken as follows: 
Waist- laying flat, taken across the back waistband, then doubled
Hips- laying flat, with the tape measure at the bottom of the zip or button fly, then doubled
Rise- from the crotch seam to the top of the waistband
Inseam- from the crotch seam inside the leg to the hem
Vintage high waisted jeans have a very different fit than modern jeans. Most high waist styles have a rise (the distance from the crotch to the waistband) of 11-12". Modern jeans typically have a 7-8" rise.  Shorts are listed according to the actual measured waist size in inches, NOT the tag size.

Product name: ONE COLOR OMBRE / 100% Cotton Dog Leash//4 foot dog leash//ombre dog leash//custom dog leash//dog lead//Rope dog leash//Christmas Dog Leash
Description:
This listing is for a single (1) color ombre leash. Every leash fades into the natural cotton color.
PLEASE READ FULL DESCRIPTION BEFORE ORDERING.
PRODUCT: 
Our leashes are made of 100% cotton rope and colored using pet safe dyes. They are soft and comfortable, yet very durable. We use heavy duty bolt snaps that firmly secure your pet's collar. 100% cotton twine is used to secure all splices (loops) and is dyed to match your leash. 
PROCESS: 
Each item is custom made. Every rope leash is first spliced and whipped by hand then individually dyed. Please let me know BEFORE you order if you need an item by a particular date.
CARE:
Our leashes may be spot-washed in cold water only with a mild detergent and laid out to dry. Cotton can shrink when wet so please keep a close eye on your leash while it dries. If shrinking occurs, pulling on it gently while wet should bring it back to it's original length.
SIZES:
Our leashes come in two different widths: 3/8 inch and 1/2 inch.
-1/2 inch is recommended for pets 50 pounds and over.
-3/8 inch is recommended for pets up to 50 pounds. However if you have a strong puller or heavy chewer you may want to choose the 1/2 inch leash for a little extra durability.
IMPORTANT INFO. PLEASE READ BEFORE ORDERING.
**Cotton has a tendency to shrink and expand naturally depending on weather conditions and moisture. Please take this into consideration when using this product. We are not responsible for any shrinking/expanding that occurs during the shipping process or during use after sent to buyer. 
**Colors may look slightly different than pictured. We try to get our photos as accurate as possible. Please take this into consideration when placing your order. In addition, because every item is custom made, no two items are exactly the same and the item you order may vary slightly from the photo. 
**Please note that no leash is indestructible. Keep a close watch for wear and tear and replace when necessary. We will not be responsible for any mishaps that may occur due to the use of our product; the buyer is solely responsible for the product after it is shipped.

Description:
The perfect care package to send someone who is grieving. 
Lynneys Comforts are a wonderful gift to send a friend or family member to help soothe them during any stage of grief. The five piece set includes Lavender Bath Salts, Lavender Cream, Lavender Essential Oil Pulse Point Roll-on, Scented Candle and a Gel Beaded Hot/Cold Eye Mask.

Help them through their grief with this beautiful guided journal by Beth Marshall who wrote this after losing close family members. Only after writing and connecting with other people experiencing grief, she realized a joy-filled life after loss really is possible. 
All items are beautifully packaged in a gift box and include a card on how to use the products as well as a personalized gift card from you. Please include a note how you would like your name to read for the Gift Card.

Product name: String of Pearls - Senecio rowleyanus - 6" Hanging Basket
Description:
String of pearls hanging basket. Great for gardens, patios, or indoors window sill.  Senecio rowleyanus, commonly known as string-of-pearls or string-of-beads, is a creeping, perennial, succulent vine belonging to the family Asteraceae. This plant was named after British botanist Gordon Douglas Rowley who specialized in Cactaceae and succulents. It is native to the drier parts of southwest Africa. In its natural environment its stems trail on the ground, rooting where they touch and forming dense mats. It often avoids direct sunlight by growing in the shade of other plants and rocks.
Fertilizer: Use either a balanced or low-nitrogen formula at low levels, but frequently---March through October. Soil: Should be loose and porous like a cactus soil.
Succulents are grown in dry, arid climates, so it is important to make sure they have a good drainage with soil that is specifically designed for succulents.   Reduce watering in fall and winter to once or twice a month depending on your climate.
You will receive String of pearls hanging basket similar to pictures above.
Hanging basket size: 4.25 inches deep, 6 inches circumference. 
Succulents need the sun to survive; take them out of the box as soon as you receive them.
Instructions to care for your plants will be included in package.
If you are ordering from areas below 35 degrees, we have 72 hour heat packs available for purchase to protect your plants during transit.
Before checking out, please make sure your address is correct or else your shipment may be delayed.
We want you to be happy with your order. Please message us if there are any questions or concerns. We will respond promptly. 
Happy planting!

Product name: Greyt Greyhound Stone Art (donation to Greyhound Welfare) Verdigris, Pet Lover Gift, Greyhound Rescue
Description:
Pictured here is my sculpture, Greyt Greyhound, capturing the fastest dog in cast stone. My original design was hand-carved, and this example cast from a mold I made of my original plaster bas relief carving. It is 3" by 8 3/4" and weighs a pound. I will hand cast your Greyt Greyhound in my home studio.  Cast stone is a combination of mineral oxide pigments, C-144 masonry sand, marble dust, and blends of white and gray portland cements. Once cured, I will process your sculpture with a complex collection of metallic and interference colors over a black base (Finish A 7 12 31). Interference paints create subtle changes in color based on the type and direction of light. The mineral oxide pigments I use in my finishes are 100% permanent and lightfast. Greyt Greyhound is further protected from the elements by a UV barrier coating.

Product name: Montessori Silent E Reading Blocks, Educational Toy, Beginning Reader Tools, Long Vowel, Magic E
Description:
These blocks are great for introducing Silent E to young readers. Once your child has mastered reading the three-letter Phonetic Reading Blocks, introduce these Silent E blocks. Your child will love twisting the end block to reveal and hide the Silent E to create words with both short and long vowel sounds.  
Easy to use, first show the child a 3 letter phonetic word of your choice. Have the child read the word. Then, twist the block so that the "e" appears at the end of the word. Explain to the child that in this word, the "e" does not make a sound, but it does have a job. Tell the child that the "e" makes the vowel say it's name. For example: man becomes mane, fad becomes fade and so on. Practice reading the new word together. Show the child another word with the same vowel. Continue reading words in this manner, helping when necessary and eventually moving on to other vowels.
The blocks allow practice with all 5 vowel sounds plus 12 different consonants and 1 phonogram. Each rod includes 4 phonetic words  4 silent E words, giving your little reader a total of 40 words to read over and over. All words are in the dictionary. A fun tool to strengthen and improve your child's self-confidence with reading and use of long vowel sounds.
Made to replace or compliment your Montessori Silent E Word Cards. The letters are written in lower case d'nealian print with red consonants and blue vowels, in order to match the rest of your Montessori Language materials. A must have language work for the Montessori 3-6 year old classroom.
Handmade with natural unfinished wood and non-toxic ink and glue. Sets may have slight imperfections/variations since each one is handmade & unique.

Includes:
5 Reading Block Rods with middle sounds A,E,I,O,& U. Each one is 4.5 inches long by 3/4 inch wide. 
1 Playing Instruction Card
CHOKING HAZARD: Small parts. Not for children under 3 years old.
Created with Love by a Certified Montessori Teacher. ALL RIGHTS RESERVED

Description:
****************************************
Why we honor and insist on hand sew our leather product ?
Leather sewing machines commonly use the "lock stitch" , If just one loop of a lock stitch is broken, the other side will automatically be loosened, often this process of unraveling will continue until the entire product is ruined.
Hand sewing (saddle stitch) will not unravel if one loop is broken.
Though slower, hand sewing is superior to machine sewing. It is the best way to sew leather together,the hand-sew leather product will be more durable and stand the test of time !!

Product name: Dying Poet by L.M. Gottschalk Published by Eclisple Publishing Co. Philadelphia 1907
Description:
Description: Antique sheet music, Dying Poet by L.M. Gottschalk, 1907.  Cool gothic graphics. Unusual theme would make a great framed conversation piece.
Dimensions (approximate): 10-1/4 x 13-1/2 inches
Condition: Fair condition. 102 year old antique paper sheet music which has soiling, stains, tears and marks from use. Back and front cover separated by tear. Please look at the pictures carefully before placing your order.
History: By the 1860s, Gottschalk had established himself as the best known pianist in the New World. In May 1865, he was mentioned in a San Francisco newspaper as having "travelled 95,000 miles by rail and given 1,000 concerts". Gottschalk chose to travel to South America, where he continued to give frequent concerts. During one of these concerts, in Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, on November 24, 1869, he collapsed from having contracted yellow fever. Just before his collapse, he had finished playing his romantic piece Morte! (translated from Brazilian Portuguese as "Death"), although the actual collapse occurred just as he started to play his celebrated piece Tremolo. Gottschalk never recovered from the collapse. Three weeks later, on December 18, 1869, at the age of 40, he died at his hotel in Tijuca, Rio de Janeiro, probably from an overdose of quinine.
Citation: Louis Moreau Gottschalk. (2016, July 2). In Wikipedia, The Free Encyclopedia. Retrieved 14:38, July 4, 2016

Product name: Things We Don't Talk About: Women's Stories from the Red Tent
Description:
Things We Don’t Talk About: Woman’s Stories from the Red Tent is a groundbreaking 72-minute documentary film by award winning filmmaker Isadora Gabrielle Leidenfrost, PhD. Spontaneous and organic, a Red Tent is a red textile space where women gather to rest, renew, and often share deep and powerful stories about their lives. The Red Tent movement is changing the way that women interact and support each other by providing a place that honors and celebrates women, and by enabling open conversations about the things that women don’t want to talk about in other venues. Things We Don’t Talk About weaves together healing narratives from inside the Red Tent to shine a spotlight on this vital, emergent women’s tradition. The film provides us an opportunity to remember, to listen, to know, and to find what it is we need to bring back to our communities to help awaken the voices of women.
This DVD is subtitled in Spanish, French, German, Portuguese, Hebrew, and English (cc). This film is intended for a mature audience.

Product name: EVA - v neck lace dress, bridal, wedding dress grosgrain ribbon tied at the waist - chic city wedding - full length, long sz10 Ready to Wear
Description:
Hello!
I’m Anna, a designer and dressmaker based near Brighton in the UK. I design and make every dress here in my home studio at the seaside for my bridal wear label; ‘This Modern Love’. 
About This Modern Love
The aesthetic for ‘This Modern Love’ is romantic, feminine, bohemian and beautifully simple dresses, all hand crafted using the finest materials such as silk chiffon, corded lace, duchess satin and soft tulle.  My dresses are designed in a delicate colour palette including of ivory, nude and blush tones, though lots more colours are available.
All of my dresses are a relaxed, pull on style which cinch in at the waist with elastic - they are not structured or fitted. Because of this, my designs feel comfortable, lightweight and fluid. My customers are often women looking for a relaxed, vintage style or bohemian dress, with a woodland, rustic or festival theme to their wedding: brides looking for something simple, beautiful and original.
Highlights for This Modern Love
Featured in the VOGUE Wedding Wishlist (Dec 2016)
Named as ‘The One to Watch’ in Perfect Wedding Magazine (Apr 2016)
Finalist at the UK Wedding Awards for Best Bridesmaid Collection 2016 (You and Your Wedding & Hitched.co.uk) (Jan 2016)
Featured in Elle Magazine, Vogue Italia, Style and The Bride, The Bohemian Wedding, Hochzeitswahn, The Wedding Bazaar, Bespoke Bride, Love Sussex Weddings,  Save The Date, Love Our Wedding, Oh Comely, Little Book for Brides and Etsy’s Editor Picks.
Winner of the Elle Magazine & Warehouse Talent Spot 2013
Featured supplier at the Etsy Wedding Fair (London, June 2015)
About this dress
EVA READY TO WEAR BRIDAL GOWN - GREY SILK AND  GUIPIERE LACE BRIDAL GOWN
A classic, elegant simple bridal gown 
Made with 100% grey silk and ivory guipiere lace overlay
Dress features a simple V neckline, a deep V at the back 
Finished with an ivory grosgrain ribbon tied at the waist.
Sz small approx UK 10. 
Tall - long length
(Model is 5ft 11 & 2" heels and sz 10)
A very pretty dress for a woodlands wedding or a romantic elopement
Like all This Modern Love dresses, this design is a simple, unstructured pull on design. It simply pulls on over the head and cinches at the waist with elastic, there are no fastenings, zips etc. The design is relaxed and non fitted. 
Ready to wear dresses
This listing is for the dress pictured in the photographs, it’s a ‘ready to wear’ dress which means that the dress is the size listed only. This style is not currently available as a ‘made to order/bespoke’ dress as the fabric used to create it is no longer available.
Want to try it on? That’s absolutely fine! You’re welcome to order the dress to try it and if it’s not suitable then you can return the dress for a full refund. Returns must be notified within a strict 7 day period of the receipt of the dress. I’m sorry, but postage costs are non refundable. If you’d like more information, measurements or photos of the dress to check whether it will be suitable then please let me know and I will be happy to assist.
Can I visit your studio?
Yes! I have a home studio which you are welcome to visit to try on the dresses. Please contact me to make an appointment. I’m based on the regency parade on Worthing seafront which is approximately 20 minutes from Brighton (UK). Studio details provided upon request.
Like to know more?
You can read more about my designs, highlights, background, FAQs and testimonials from real brides on my website & take a look at my portfolio of work on my social media too on Wordpress, Pinterest, Facebook, Instagram & Twitter.
www.thismodernlovebridal.com
Anna

Product name: USA made Tahkli Indian-Style Support Spindle Coin Takli
Description:
This little Indian-style metal support spindle is approximately 7" long and weighs 18g.  There is a flattened hook at the top that is very well designed:  It can be used to start a leader by slipping a small amount of fiber around the hook, and the leader thread naturally falls into this 45 degree notch while spinning when spiraled up the shaft.  Also, the flattened hook's profile places the leader as close to the center of rotation as possible.  Although this spindle can be used as a drop spindle, it is most efficient when used as a support spindle.  It is best used for spinning fine, short fibers such as cotton, bison, camel down, yak down, and cashmere.  It is also good for long slippery fibers like silk.  Handmade in the USA, this is the finest tahkli I have spun on, with exceptional balance and speed.  Stamped on the bottom by the master metalsmith as seen in photo #2.
Metals:  black painted steel shaft and brass whorl
**NOTE: Price is for one metal tahkli, wooden support bowl not included.

Description:
Make Skull Mask, 3D mask, Face,PDF, Pattern mask, Polygon DIY Paper Mask, Papercraft,Template,Printable Skull, Halloween, paper Helmet,Party
Pages: 15
 Difficulty: medium
 What do I get if I buy one of your products?
You will get:
- Instant download file containing mask pattern and instructions
- Instructions in English
- Help File with illustration of the building steps 
- Fitting instructions.
Are the masks coloured?
No, our mask patterns are not coloured. You need to glue the patterns on the cardboard of your choice. You can make your color choice by buying coloured cardboard. This is the way we assemble our masks that you see in the listings.
What do I need to build my mask?
You just need a few basic supplies that you may already have at home:
- A printer (A4 or US letter size)
- Sheets of A4/letter size paper or cardboard
(we recommend thicker paper or thin cardboard (160-300g), it`s up to you. or thin cardboard)
- Scissors
- Craft Knife (optional)
- Ruler
- Glue
- Tape
- Needle
Sizing
The mask pattern that you are buying is designed to fit an adult and you should not need to adjust the scaling. Please print the file at 100% the same size as the original document. If you want to use this template for children, you can scale it down to 80% using your printer settings.
Paint the finished mask, as you like to create your own personal design)
Submit shots of your completed mask at https://www.instagram.com/_shame_shame/ or view what others have been doing!
Have you problems? Сontact with me.
Lots of effort has gone into the creation of the design template. The masks were physically constructed several times and the template has been improved by looking at the model to get the best final result. You can use the template to make as many masks as you want but we request you to kindly not use the template for commercial purposes or share the templates with anyone.
We are grateful for your feedback, you can help us become better!

Description:

************************************************************
The rings are created from solid sterling silver or solid 14k yellow gold.  I use round wire to create the band, but forge a small section at the top flat.  It is on this flattened area that I stamp the word of your choice.  I am now offering 2 different size styles:
Teeny Tiny is about 1mm tall with a TINY 1mm lettering.  (Very tiny!!)
Little Bigger is about 1.5mm tall with a little 1.5mm lettering. 
The rings are TINY by design, with TINY lettering meant to be subtle.  This style of ring will only fit up to 10 character spaces.  Keep in mind that they make look large on your computer screen, but they are tiny :)

Product name: Sheffield Snow Globe Necklace - Sheffield landmarks - Sheffield necklace - architecture - Yorkshire - skyline - snow globe jewellery
Description:
Sheffield landmarks old and new adorn the glittery snow filled landscape of our Sheffield snow globe necklace, including the Crucible, Winter Gardens, and the fondly remembered looming chimneys of Tinsley Viaduct. 
We asked local Sheffield residents for their favourite buildings and landmarks to adorn this Yorkshire skyline. Can you identify their top picks?
From our illustrations we created a new view of Sheffield placing the iconic architecture together.   Our snow globe began as a series of drawings which we then combined digitally.  These are fed to Bertha, our laser cutter, who transferred their outlines onto FSC certified Birch wood.  We then hand painted each element using beautiful pearlescent mica-infused inks to make the city skyline pop.
Mixing 3 types of glitter to create the perfect snowy dew over the city gives our snow globes extra glisten and sparkle. 
The city is cut from FSC certified birch plywood and the Sheffield name plaque is cut from FSC certified solid cedar wood, with the globe itself cut from clear acrylic.
We'll post the globe to you in one of our wax sealed boxes, hand stamped by team Frilly.
Keep an eye out for our every growing collection of city snowglobe necklaces.  Our first, Birmingham, is shown in photo 4.
Snow globe measures:
w 7.8cm
d 1cm
h 6cm
Chain length approximately 20" silver plated.

Description:
Charming personalized name bracelet for mom that will be hand stamped with your children's names or grandchildren's names. It would be a great mom bracelet or grandmother bracelet. You can also add friends, family or even your pets! 
PERSONALIZATION:
★ PLEASE INCLUDE AT CHECKOUT IN "Note to seller" box: ★
*Name to be stamped on the charm, or charms. 
*Birthstone month(s) that coordinate with each name. You get one birthstone for each name charm you order.

◆Q: Can I add extra birthstones/or accent beads to a bracelet?
A: Absolutely! Each bracelet comes standard with 1 accent bead. To add additional birthstones/accent beads you can purchase the link below along with the bracelet:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/80300824/add-a-swarovski-crystal-birthstone?ref=shop_home_feat
◆Q: Can you stamp something on the back of the pendant?
A: Sorry, but I can only stamp on one side of a pendant...otherwise I've found that the stamping runs the risk of showing through onto the front. Sorry about that.
Q: Can I include a note in the package so that I can send it directly as a gift?
A: Absolutely, it's no problem at all to include a short note for you in the package. Just type me a quick note during checkout of what you want the note to say.
Q: If I place an order today, how soon will my order ship? 
A: Always check the shop announcement at the top of my main page to see the current turn around times.
Q:What size is the pendant?
A: Check the sizing in the description of each piece of jewelry. Also, click on the arrows on the photos to see additional photos. 
Q: What are the hand-stamped pendants made out of?
A: My hand-stamped, quote pieces are made using brushed aluminum. Aluminum is very hypoallergenic and those that are even allergic to sterling silver and other metals can usually wear aluminum without any problems. 
Q: Can you make a custom necklace/custom quote for me?
A: I love custom orders! Convo me and let me know what you had in mind and I will see if it's something I can design for you. :)

These have a medium high waist that range from 11-13" rise, they sit just above the hip bone, on most.
These are high waist, vintage 70s-90s in your custom size, favorite color, flattering cut and tatter choice. We get our customers(see reviews) a "these were made for me" fit when they provide their measurements.
Vintage Levi's brand shorts. These babes have been hand-cut, distressed and artfully frayed to perfection. 
These have a high waist and medium-high cut.

******* PLEASE FILL THIS OUT WITH YOUR ORDER: http://firegypsyvintage.com/pages/levis-shorts-size
* Please note these take 5-7 days to custom-fit then 2-3 days to ship.
* 501's are extra  a which are harder to find/more rare, button-fly, slimmer fit, thicker denim and more collectable.
(The 501 has a button fly front instead of the zipper, is has a slimmer fit and is good for less curvy body types. It is Levi's classic style since the 1800s.  
They are harder to find and more sought after they actually gain value with age and are now becoming collectable. The denim is a bit thicker. If you are purchasing these shorts for a trip or event and won't wear them much, I would suggest the regular Levi's. If you want to wear them alot and keep them for years, I would suggest the 501's.)

THIS LISTING IS FOR LEVIS ONLY! Please measure yourself carefully using a measuring tape. Your waist measurement is at the belly button area. Hip measurements are about where a pair of low rise jeans would hit. These are CUSTOM ORDER! This means I may or may not have your size in stock. if I do not have your size, I will find it for you ASAP. No additional cost. I can make your shorts any inseam, rise, length (from top of short to bottom) and you have the option of cut off style or the popular rolled look. PLEASE NOTE that the shorts in the pictures are examples of different washes-- they are not available for purchase as they have already been sold. All washes vary. Shorts vary from a mid rise to a super high rise. Some shorts may be 1% spandex and others 100% cotton.  You may request what rise you would prefer and what style Levi.
I restock most sizes at least 3-4 days a week. feel free to message me first to see if I have the exact shorts you want before ordering. 
BEFORE ORDERING PLEAST PROVIDE THE FOLLOWING MEASUREMENTS IF POSSIBLE--
using a measuring tape measure around your waist (where your navel is), your low waist (right below the navel), hips and thighs. Let me know if you want them a longer to be able to roll or more of a cut off. 
If you need them by a certain date please note! Always feel free to email me @  nance6887 [!at] aol.com. Thank you!!  :).    
                    If you unsure of how to measure your waist properly here is a link that will show you-- http://m.wikihow.com/Measure-Your-Waist
                                                             
I run this shop completely alone:)  This is why there is such a long wait for your order to be shipped. So sorry for long it takes- I try to get orders out as fast as possible! :) Trust me, it will be worth the wait! :)
